pared baking trays, drizzle with oil and bake for 5-7 minutes (200°C) until just browned. Remove baking trays from oven and carefully turn over pitas and bake for a further 5-7 minutes (200°C) until just browned.  Allow to cool slightly, then cut into halves and carefully slice open lengthways to form a pocket. Fill with your choice of filling and serve warm (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To make your own rice flours, place 250 g rice into mixing bowl and mill <strong>2 min\/speed 10<\/strong>. Use as needed.<strong> <\/strong>","Serve pita pockets with Lamb kleftiko, tzatziki dip and Greek salad. Please refer to the Lamb kleftiko recipe on this recipe chip."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 15m","8 portions"]}